# Metamorfosis LLC — Cursor Rules

## Always read first

Before any task, read the relevant docs in /docs/ based on what you're working on.
Never start coding without a written plan approved by the user.

## Tech stack

Next.js 16, React 19, TypeScript strict, Supabase, Square (production), Shippo, Zustand, TanStack Query, react-hook-form + Zod, Tailwind 4, shadcn/ui

## Code rules

- Max 200 lines per file. Split if bigger.
- No `any` types. No magic numbers. No inline business logic in JSX.
- All API routes: Zod `.strict()` validation first, then logic.
- Naming: kebab-case files, PascalCase components, camelCase functions, SCREAMING_SNAKE constants.
- Comments and code in English only.

## Git

- Never commit to main. Always branch: feat/, fix/, refactor/
- Commit messages present-tense: "add Square sync engine"
- No console.log, no commented-out code, no unused imports in commits.

## Design

- Dark mode only. Base bg: oklch(0.16 0.005 280)
- Accents: violet, amber, emerald, rose, sand — max 2 in one viewport.
- `<img loading="lazy">` for all product images. `<Image>` from next/image for heroes only (max 50 total).
- Square CDN images: use `getSquareImageUrl(url, width)` utility — never fetch original.

## Critical rules

- Square is PRODUCTION. Payment mode is test during dev (NEXT_PUBLIC_PAYMENT_MODE=test).
- Never invent SKUs, prices, weights, or data.
- Image fallback: variation.imageUrl → parent.imageUrl → <PlaceholderImage />
- No external placeholder services (Unsplash, Picsum, etc.)
- Domain-dependent config is deferred. Don't block on it.
